└─ Integration: Cleanroom ISO 6

Line 2: Quantum payload production
├─ Cleanroom: ISO 4 (1000m²)
├─ Workstations: 20 parallel assembly stations
├─ Testing: 4 vacuum chambers for final test
├─ Calibration: Quantum characterization setup
└─ Yield target: 90% pass final test

Line 3: Integration and test
├─ Thermal vacuum: 2 chambers (3m diameter)
├─ Vibration: 2 shakers (up to 2000kg)
├─ EMI/EMC: Anechoic chamber
├─ Optical alignment: Collimator for pointing test
└─ Final acceptance: 7-day continuous test

Production Schedule (12 satellites):
├─ Month 1-3: First bus completed
├─ Month 4-6: First payload completed
├─ Month 7: First satellite integrated
├─ Month 8: Environmental testing
├─ Month 9-20: Remainder at 1 satellite/month
└─ Month 21-24: Spares and ground testing

Quality Control:
├─ Component level: 100% screening
├─ Module level: Burn-in at 125°C for 168h
├─ Satellite level: Thermal cycling (-40°C to +70°C, 10 cycles)
├─ Vibration: Qualification levels (14.1Grms random)
└─ Final: 240h continuous operation test
```

